<http://data.open.ac.uk/ontology/news-classification/examples-4.1.1> rdf:type owl:Ontology ;
    skos:note """
    Letâ€™s consider first the case in which a relation between entities (e.g., business links between a politician and a business person) is the focus of a news item.  This situation can be handled as shown below, where we use a domain relation to express the business connection between the two people and then we take advantage of our reification mechanism.  

    s2: hasBusinessConnection (politician1 businessperson1) 

    s3: hasTopic (ni55342 T(s2)) 
    """@en ;
    skos:note """
    The axioms must infer the following:
     [...]
    """@en
    .

:politician1 a owl:Thing ;
    :hasBusinessConnection :businessperson1
    .
:businessperson1 a owl:Thing .


:ni55342 a nco:NewsItem ;
    nco:hasTopic :ts2 .

:ts2 nco:isTopicRoleOf :s2 .

:s2 a nco:Statement ;
    nco:subject :politician1 ;
    nco:object :businessperson1 ;
    nco:predicate :hasBusinessConnection
    .
    
:s3 a nco:Statement ;
    nco:subject :ni55342 ;
    nco:object :ts2 ;
    nco:predicate :hasTopic
    .